<br>
For example:<br>
Increasing your AC from 1100 to 1200 would result in a drop of 10 DPS in mob damage in a particular encounter.<br>
<br>
Increasing your AC from 1300 to 1400 would result in a negligible change in mob damage for the same encounter.<br>
<br>
The generally accepted AC softcap is 1250. <p><div align="center" style="font-size: 11px; font-family: arial"><img src="http://www.bfdesigns.net/eq/wandor_sig.jpg"><br><a target="_blank" href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=6103"><b>Wandor</b></a> | <a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=6102" target="_blank"><b>Moordian</b></a> | <a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=353608" target="_blank"><b>Wandorfu</b></a><br><a target="_blank" href="http://www.exarch.net/"><b>Fusion of Flame</b></a></div></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/ukhumak.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Khumak</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 49<br> <font color=#FF0000>(9/20/02 10:32:38 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3942.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.steelwarrior.org/forum/p_ac.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: AC softcap</span><hr size=1> I have a somewhat related question about Combat Stability.  Now that I have ND3 and am closing in on AE taunt I've been eyeing CS, CA, and PE.  <br>
